name: Separation Anxiety Disorder
description:
Inpired color by Witjk

a disorder that occurs when a person feels excessively anxious as a result of the home or from someone who has strong emotions with the person with this disorder (such as a parent, family, spouse, or sibling). This disorder most often occurs in toddlers and young children, generally from 6-7 months to 3 years of age, although this disorder can also appear pathologically in children, adolescents, and adults.
